**Expected Behavior**:

`ForEachStatementInfo.ElementType` should return `System.Linq.IGrouping<string?, object>`

**Actual Behavior**:

foreach expression type is `System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable<System.Linq.IGrouping<string?, object>>`

`ForEachStatementInfo.ElementType` returns `System.Linq.IGrouping<string, object>`, i.e. nullability is missing

Related to #68785

For a scenario like `T[] arr = [..elem1, ..elem2]`, we should consider emitting a branch like the following:

```cs
var elem1Temp = elem1;
var elem2Temp = elem2;
var length = elem1Temp.Length + elem2Temp.Length;
T[] arr;
if (length == 0)
{
    arr = Array.Empty<T>();
}
else
{
    arr = new T[length];
    // ... populate the array
}
```
